# Run `cargo fmt` Before Committing

Before creating any git commit in this repository, always run `cargo fmt`
and stage any resulting changes as part of the same commit. This keeps
formatting noise out of subsequent commits and avoids CI fmt failures.

## Workflow

```bash
cargo fmt
git add -A
git commit -m "..."
```

If `cargo fmt` touches files unrelated to your change, include them in
the same commit rather than creating a separate formatting commit — the
project's history treats formatting as part of the logical change that
introduced it.

## Verification

`cargo fmt --check` should exit 0 on the final tree before committing.
If it does not, run `cargo fmt` and re-stage.
